{
  "version": "0.4",
  "title": "XCP Service: Event & Performance Photography — Sub-page",
  "type": "page",
  "content": [
    {
      "id": "event_hero",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {
        "_title": "Event Photography Hero",
        "layout": "full_width",
        "background_image": {
          "url": "[uc_local]assets/images/event-photography-hero.jpg"
        },
        "content_position": "middle"
      },
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "event_hero_col",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 100
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "event_eyebrow",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>Event & Performance Photography</p>"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "event_title",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Capturing the Energy, the Moment, the Night",
                "header_size": "h1",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "event_subtitle",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>Event and performance photography for corporate launches, music events, exhibitions, theatre, and live performance. Fast delivery, professional quality, and coverage that makes your audience feel as though they were there.</p>"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "event_cta_button",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "button",
              "settings": {
                "text": "Enquire About Event Coverage",
                "link": {
                  "url": "/contact",
                  "is_external": false,
                  "nofollow": false
                },
                "align": "center"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "event_overview",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {
        "_title": "Event Photography Overview",
        "layout": "boxed",
        "structure": "20"
      },
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "event_overview_image_col",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 40,
            "_column_size_tablet": 100,
            "_column_size_mobile": 100
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "event_overview_image",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "image",
              "settings": {
                "image": {
                  "url": "[uc_local]assets/images/event-photography-overview.jpg"
                },
                "image_size": "large"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "event_overview_text_col",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 60,
            "_column_size_tablet": 100,
            "_column_size_mobile": 100
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "event_overview_heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Events, Launches, Music & Performance",
                "header_size": "h2"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "event_overview_text",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>Events happen once. The photography of them lasts forever — or fails to capture anything meaningful at all. XCP Photography brings experience in low-light environments, fast-moving subjects, and the instinct to anticipate the decisive moment before it happens.</p><p>From corporate award ceremonies to intimate jazz performances, from brand launch parties to large-scale music festivals, the approach is the same: quiet, unobtrusive, technically prepared, and completely focused on telling the story of the night.</p><ul><li>Corporate events, conferences, and award ceremonies</li><li>Music concerts and live performance</li><li>Theatre, dance, and arts events</li><li>Brand launches, product reveals, and PR events</li><li>Exhibition and gallery opening coverage</li><li>Same-day and next-morning turnaround options for press use</li><li>Full-resolution delivery via private gallery link</li></ul>"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "event_music_note",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {
        "_title": "Music Photography Note",
        "layout": "boxed"
      },
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "event_music_col",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 100
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "event_music_heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Music Photography — A Specialism, Not a Side Note",
                "header_size": "h3",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "event_music_text",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>Xavier has been photographing live music for over a decade — from small club nights to major festival stages. He understands the rhythm of a performance, the relationship between artist and audience, and the technical demands of working in venue lighting that most photographers find challenging.</p><p>Music photography commissions are available for artists, labels, promoters, and venues.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "event_closing_cta",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {
        "_title": "Event Photography Closing CTA",
        "layout": "boxed"
      },
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "event_closing_col",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 100,
            "text_align": "center"
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "event_closing_heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Tell Me About Your Event",
                "header_size": "h2",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "event_closing_text",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>The earlier we talk, the better the outcome. Tell me your date, location, and what you need — I will confirm availability and send a proposal within 24 hours.</p>"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "event_closing_button",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "button",
              "settings": {
                "text": "Enquire About Your Event",
                "link": {
                  "url": "/contact",
                  "is_external": false,
                  "nofollow": false
                },
                "align": "center"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
